<!-- Main Contents -->	
	
<table width="1160" border="0"><tr><td width="293" height="321"><img src="../Pictures/elephant.png" width="291" height="319" alt="Cheetahs Photo"></td><td width="857"><p id ="main_contents">Elephants can tear down huge tree limbs or pick up small objects with their muscular trunks.<br><br>Their trunks are used also to squirt water on their backs or into their mouths. Also the trunks<br><br>are used to blow dirt on their back during dust baths.<br><br><br><strong>Size:</strong> The male elephants grow to be 21 feet in length and are about 10 feet tall and weigh<br><br>up to 11,000 pounds. Females elephants are only 8 1/2 feet tall and weigh less than their<br><br>counterpart (the male elephant).<br><br><br><strong>Habitat:</strong> Elephants like the tropical forests which are moist. Also, they like the evergreen<br><br>lowland forest to the cooler mountain forests.<br><br><br><strong>National Zoo Diet:</strong> Each day at the Zoo, elephants eat 125 pounds of hay, ten pounds of<br><br>vegetables and fruits, and a few leafy branches.</p></td></tr></table></div></div>
	
